munities as citizen soldiers  in times of peace and in times of deepest peril  THE VMI FOUNDATION Neikirk Hall   304 Letcher Avenue   Lexington  VA 24450 P O  Box 932   Lexington  VA 24450 P  800 444 1839   540 464 7328 F  540 463 2695 give vmiaa org VMI Foundation   Reunion Funds  skip to content VMI VMI Alumni Keydet Club Webcams Directories Login Menu About Us Priorities About Giving Thanks   Recognition Stewardship Videos Give Close Menu About Us Priorities About Giving Thanks   Recognition Stewardship Videos Give VMI FOUNDATION Neikirk Hall   304 Letcher Avenue P O  Box 932   Lexington  VA 24450 P  800 444 1839   540 464 7328 F  540 464 4545 give vmiaa org   Reunion Campaigns Reunion Campaigns are special to the respective class and the Institute in that it is a unique opportunity to contribute to the quality of life at the Institute  Alumni donate most of their gifts and pledges in support of VMI  Many of those gifts are generated through annual Reunion Funds organized by the classes that are celebrating their 10th  25th  and 50th reunions  Donors to these funds   who often include spouses  children  and friends   participate in many ways  planned giving  gifts to Annual Giving s three funds  VMI Foundation Fund  Keydet Club Scholarship Fund or Athletic Operations Fund  or restricted gifts to specific programs  Classes may even create special funds associated with their reunions  such as unrestricted endowments or scholarships   These special funds offer Brother Rats special opportunities to come together in support of VMI  For more information  contact  Marilyn Dudley Associate Director of Annual and Reunion Giving Ph  800 444 1839 ext  239        Email mdudley vmiaa org  or   John J  Wranek Vice President for Alumni and Reunion Giving Ph  800 444 1839  ext  244        Email  jwranek vmiaa org VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI UNCOMMON PURPOSE   In 1839  VMI set an uncommon course  to prepare young people for lives of service  leade