Institute in that it is a unique opportunity to contribute to the quality of life at the Institute  Alumni donate most of their gifts and pledges in support of VMI  Many of those gifts are generated through annual Reunion Funds organized by the classes that are celebrating their 10th  25th  and 50th reunions  Donors to these funds   who often include spouses  children  and friends   participate in many ways  planned giving  gifts to Annual Giving s three funds  VMI Foundation Fund  Keydet Club Scholarship Fund or Athletic Operations Fund  or restricted gifts to specific programs  Classes may even create special funds associated with their reunions  such as unrestricted endowments or scholarships   These special funds offer Brother Rats special opportunities to come together in support of VMI  For more information  contact  Marilyn Dudley Associate Director of Annual and Reunion Giving Ph  800 444 1839 ext  239        Email mdudley vmiaa org  or   John J  Wranek Vice President for Alumni and Reunion Giving Ph  800 444 1839  ext  244        Email  jwranek vmiaa org Reunion Campaigns Reunion Campaigns are special to the respective class and the Institute in that it is a unique opportunity to contribute to the quality of life at the Institute  Alumni donate most of their gifts and pledges in support of VMI  Many of those gifts are generated through annual Reunion Funds organized by the classes that are celebrating their 10th  25th  and 50th reunions  Donors to these funds   who often include spouses  children  and friends   participate in many ways  planned giving  gifts to Annual Giving s three funds  VMI Foundation Fund  Keydet Club Scholarship Fund or Athletic Operations Fund  or restricted gifts to specific programs  Classes may even create special funds associated with their reunions  such as unrestricted endowments or scholarships   These special funds offer Brother Rats special opportunities to come together in support of VMI For more information  contact Marilyn